cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.DC 

This paper discusses covert communication techniques in Named Data Networking (NDN), which is a content-centric approach to networking. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses security and privacy concerns, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The techniques proposed in the paper rely on network-layer services, which could place it in cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the use of in-network caches and routers' forwarding state, which could suggest it belongs to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper discusses the feasibility and performance of the proposed techniques, which could place it in cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
